# OKF ai-docs (Open Knowledge Format)

Human prose stays under `docs/` (hdc). Agent recall lives under **`hdc-private/ai-docs/`** only (OKF v0.1). Full promote workflow: skill **`hdc-okf`** (`apps/hdc-agent-server/skills/hdc-okf/SKILL.md` or `.cursor/skills/hdc-okf/`).

## Bundle ownership

| Knowledge | Bundle | Writers |
| --- | --- | --- |
| All agent OKF (platform, package, site) | **`hdc-private/ai-docs/`** | Humans / IDE; fleet `hdc-sre-ops`, `hdc-manager`, `hdc-sre-engineer` |

hdc and hdc-clumps do **not** carry `ai-docs/`. Fleet agents still must not edit the **hdc** platform repo for code.

## Checklist when creating or editing concepts

1. **Reserved files:** `index.md` (listings; root may set `okf_version: "0.1"`) and `log.md` (newest-first ISO dates) — do not use those names for concepts.
2. **Every other `.md`:** YAML frontmatter with required non-empty `type`. Prefer `title`, `description`, `tags`, `timestamp` (ISO 8601).
3. **HDC `type` values:** `Convention`, `Architecture`, `Playbook`, `Reference`, `Gotcha`, `SiteFact`.
4. **Body:** headings, lists, tables, fenced commands — not essays. Link within the same bundle as `/path/to/concept.md`.
5. **Citations:** point at human `hdc/docs/` or authoritative `operations/` files; sibling paths in prose for cross-repo code — do not invent absolute OKF links into other repos.
6. **Indexes:** add/update the parent directory `index.md` listing when adding a concept.
7. **Log:** append a newest-first entry under root `log.md` after meaningful changes.
8. **Secrets:** env var **names** only — never secret values or full IP tables (keep `operations/ip-allocations.md` authoritative). Public hdc / hdc-clumps trees still use RFC 5737 / `example.invalid` only.

## Recall

Start at `hdc-private/ai-docs/index.md` (or `ai-docs/index.md` when the private repo is the workspace root). Prefer OKF for durable process knowledge before inventing procedures.
